-- NFL Season-Opening Game Begins After Lightning Delay in Denver
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-09-06T01:15:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-06/nfl-season-opening-game-begins-after-lightning-delay-in-denver.html
The National Football League regular
season got under way after the start of the opening game was
delayed for 44 minutes by the threat of lightning in Denver.  The game between the Broncos and the Super Bowl champion
 Baltimore Ravens  at Sports Authority Field at Mile High was
scheduled to begin at 6:30 p.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  